identificationRemarks: PMLS records list Cadlina luteomarginata complex due to challenges in field identification. However, here we recognize both Cadlina klasmalmbergi and Cadlina luteomarginata based on other confirmed observations. True Cadlina luteomarginata have more conspicuous tubercles and lack yellow glands near the mantle edge. Cadlina klasmalmbergi is more common in BC than C. luteomarginata.

identificationRemarks: Two subspecies are recognized: a Californian subspecies, Apata pricei pricei, as originally described from Monterey, California, and a Western Pacific subspecies, Apata pricei komandorica.
